            </p>

            <p class="italics">Information we collect</p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    We collect information when you register on the site, place an order, respond to a survey or communication such as name, title, company or organization,
                    e-mail address, phone number, fax number, work and/or home address, birth date, gender, information about your job function and general information about your company or organization.
                </li>
                <li>
                    We collect and store usage information about how you use our site, such as the name of your internet service provider, the browser and type of machine you
                    are using, the IP address and the website that referred you to us and the pages you visit to help manage our site.
                </li>
                <li>
                    We use cookies to manage the site and personalize your experience.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p class="italics">How we use the information collected</p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    To process and fulfill a transaction or order
                </li>
                <li>
                    To respond to your requests, inquiries, comments and concerns
                </li>
                <li>
                    To personalize your site experience and to allow us to deliver the type of content and product offerings in which you are most interested
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p class="italics">We keep visitors information secure</p>

            <p>
                We maintain reasonable administrative, technical and physical safeguards to protect the confidentiality of personal and credit information transmitted online, including but not limited to encryption, firewalls and SSL (Secure Sockets Layer).
            </p>
            
            <p class="italics">Cookies</p>

            <p>
                Cookies help us remember and process the items in your shopping cart. The information we collect through the use of cookies does allow us to know when and for how long you logged on to the website, so we can understand how to better serve your needs.
            </p>
            

            <p class="italics">Do Not Track Disclosure</p>

            <p>
                Do Not Track ("DNT") is a privacy preference that users may set in certain web browsers. DNT is intended to allow users another method of informing websites and services that they do not want certain information about their website visits collected over time and across websites.
            </p>
            
            <p class="italics">Third Parties</p>

            <p>
                Our service providers or partners may have access to your personally identifiable information as necessary to provide their services. We may also share such information with third parties in connection with the sale of a business, to enforce our Terms of Use or policies, to safeguard the security of our users and third parties, to protect our rights and property and those of third parties, and in situations where we believe we are compelled by law. In all such situations, any recipient third parties are required to maintain the privacy of all such information in their possession or control and can only use the information for the limited purpose associated with our sharing of such information. We use commercially reasonable efforts to require them to safeguard your personal information and limit their use of it. We do not sell email addresses to third parties for any purpose.
            </p>

            <p class="italics">Children's Privacy</p>

            <p>
                We do not knowingly collect information from children under the age of 13 or target the service to children under 13.
            </p>

            <p class="italics">California Privacy Rights</p>

            <p>
                Under California law, California residents may opt-out of our disclosing personal information about them to third parties for their marketing purposes. If you are a California resident
                and do not want us to disclose your information to other companies for their marketing purposes, please contact us by phone at <a href="tel:+9093918800">(909) 391-8800</a> 
                or email at <a href="mailto:customerservice@usdutygear.com">customerservice@usdutygear.com</a>. Pursuant to Section 1798.83 of the California Civil Code, residents of California have the right to request from a business, with whom the California resident has an established business relationship, certain information with respect to the types of personal information the business shares with third parties for direct marketing purposes by such third party and the identities of the third parties with whom the business has shared such information during the immediately preceding calendar year.
            </p>

            <p class="italics">Opt-out, remove or modify personal data</p>

            <p>
